sections.body:
The following example searches for documents which include a field
named `type`.

```javascript
db.fruit.aggregate([
  {
    $search: {
      "exists": {
        "path": "type"
      }
    }
  }
])
```

The above query returns the first three documents of the collection.
The document with `_id: 4` is not included because it does not have a
`type` field.

➤ Try this in the [MongoDB Search Playground](https://search-playground.mongodb.com/tools/code-sandbox/snapshots/664f77ceacd5b8b88d15cff9).

Use dot notation to search for embedded fields. The following example
searches for documents which have a field named `lemons` embedded
within a field named `quantities`.

**Input:**

```javascript
db.fruit.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "exists": {
        "path": "quantities.lemons"
      }
    }
  }
])
```

**Output:**

```javascript
{
  "_id" : 4,
  "description" : "Types of citrus fruit include lemons, oranges, and grapefruit.",
  "quantities" : {
    "lemons": 200,
    "oranges": 240,
    "grapefruit": 160
  }
}
```

➤ Try this in the [MongoDB Search Playground](https://search-playground.mongodb.com/tools/code-sandbox/snapshots/664f7892f024313ed0dbcc6e).

